    "body": "So I'm trying to work on this, but I'm stuck here. Here's the sample code I'm working with:\r\n```rust\r\nfn max_deposits_exceeded() {\r\n    let spec = MainnetEthSpec::default_spec();\r\n    let mut builder = get_builder(&spec);\r\n\r\n    let deposit_num = 7;\r\n\r\n    // need temp_state to pass it as arg in insert_deposit.\r\n    // cloning because .build() consumes the builder.\r\n    let builder_copy = builder.state_builder.clone();\r\n    let temp_state = builder_copy.build().0;\r\n\r\n    // insert deposit_num deposits\r\n    for i in 0..deposit_num {\r\n        builder.block_builder.insert_deposit(32_000_000, i as u64 , &temp_state, &spec);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    let (block, mut state) = builder.build(None, None, &spec);\r\n\r\n    let result = per_block_processing(\r\n        &mut state,\r\n        &block,\r\n        None,\r\n        BlockSignatureStrategy::VerifyIndividual,\r\n        &spec,\r\n    );\r\n\r\n    // assertion will fail\r\n    // should get a MaxDeposits error\r\n    assert_eq!(result, Ok(()));\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow obviously this code won't work, as I have not updated `eth1_data` (meaning the expected number of deposits == 0).\r\n\r\nSo I add this right after deposit_num declaration :\r\n```rust\r\n   // generate a random keypair that will serve as keys for all validators.\r\n   let keypair = Keypair::random();\r\n\r\n    // Modifying the state_builder and inserting deposit_num deposits in eth1_data.\r\n    builder.state_builder = TestingBeaconStateBuilder::from_single_keypair(deposit_num, &keypair, &spec);\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut now I'm getting\r\n```thread 'per_block_processing::tests::max_deposits_exceeded' panicked at 'called `Result::unwrap()` on an `Err` value: CommitteeCacheUninitialized(Current)', src/libcore/result.rs:999:5```\r\n\r\nSo I'm clearly missing something. Is my test architecture fine? Am I missing a step before inserting deposits? Thanks!\r\n",
